</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>Intolerance to lactose</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>Significant haematological or biochemical abnormality:</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>Haemoglobin &#x02264;8.5&#x000a0;g/dL</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>WCC &#x02264;3.5&#x02009;&#x000d7;&#x02009;10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>Neutrophils &#x02264;1.5&#x02009;&#x000d7;&#x02009;10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>Platelets &#x02264;100&#x02009;&#x000d7;&#x02009;10<sup>9</sup>/L</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>ALT &#x0003e;2 times ULN for the laboratory conducting the test.</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>Creatinine &#x0003e;1.5 times ULN for the laboratory conducting the tested</td></tr><tr valign="top"><td>eGFR &#x0003c;30&#x000a0;mL/minute</td></tr></tbody></table><table-wrap-foot><p>
